race.comment: PIERONIMO (5) is a very honest commodity who has hit the top-five at his past 12 starts and will be rock-hard fit for this. Saves his best form for this staying trip and should be right there at the business end. WILL IT SNOW (6) has placed over this track and trip and maps well for this from gate two. Top-three credentials on best figures. HAMILTON BROWN (9) is rock-hard fit now and can play a role from the inside alley. Keep very safe from the Heathcote barn. MAURITA (13) is a last-start winner here who shouldn't be underestimated despite the wide draw. BACCARAT ROUGE (4) rounds out the selections with the 2kg claim.
